info.abstract:
[Behaviour]
Converts a binary array of complex numbers expressed in polar form into the rectangular form.

[Parameters]
- input measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
                         'oph_complex_double';
                         'oph_complex_float';
                         'oph_complex_int';
                         'oph_complex_long'.
- output measure type : Ophidia typing. Supported types are:
                         'oph_complex_double';
                         'oph_complex_float';
                         'oph_complex_int';
                         'oph_complex_long'.
- measure : input measure.

[Return type]
Binary-array.

[Examples]
Get the rectangular form of an array of complex numbers expressed in polar coordinates.
oph_gsl_complex_to_rect('OPH_COMPlEX_DOUBLE','OPH_COMPLEX_DOUBLE',measure)
